translated: Åberg, Sven Folke, first engineer, Norrköping, born on July 10th, 1891 in Mjölby to inspector August Fredrik Å. and Emma Carolina Pettersson. Married in 19 with Sigrid Erlandson. Children: Sven Fredrik born in 1920, Tor in 1922, Britt in 1923. Completed high school in Lund in 1910, temporary studies at KTH (The Royal Institute of Technology) in 1911-1912, regular studies from 1912-1914, received (M) degree in 1914. Trainee at SJ (Swedish State Railways) in 1914, assistant engineer at the machinery department in Gothenburg from 1917-1924, at the machinery department in Kiruna from 1924-1929, machinery engineer at Karlskrona-Irsta-Växjö ironworks from 1930-1934, and at Växjö railway from 1935-1940. Employed at SJ since 1941, first engineer in Växjö from 1943-1946, and in Norrköping from 1946 onwards.
